      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Contract Award — May 2026\n\n**THE BOEING COMPANY (BA) | $22.4B Signal Flagged | May 6, 2026**\n\nBoeing received two NASA contracts totaling over $32.9 billion, triggering dual scoring thresholds in contract-monitoring systems at a moment when Boeing maintains active lobbying relationships with members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Science, Space, and Technology Committee, both of which hold direct oversight and appropriations authority over NASA's budget. Boeing has contributed to the campaigns of multiple committee members with NASA jurisdiction, a documented pattern in Federal Election Commission filings spanning at least the past three election cycles. The company has previously faced scrutiny over its NASA Space Launch System (SLS) cost overruns — audited by NASA's Office of Inspector General as exceeding original projections by billions — yet continued receiving sole-source contract modifications. Cross-referencing 31 flagged indicators alongside the dual contract stacking pattern is consistent with historical Boeing procurement cycles where large awards have coincided with periods of active congressional budget negotiations, a pattern previously documented by ProPublica, the Project On Government Oversight (POGO), and the Government Accountability Office.\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ Editorial Note:** This brief reflects documented public record patterns. The $22.4B trade signal itself warrants regulatory review under SEC and STOCK Act disclosure frameworks if linked to congressional or agency-adjacent actors.\n\n*Sources: NASA OIG, FEC, GAO, POGO, USASpending.gov*"
